events.title: Major Fire, Ocala National Forest, Florida, United States
Flood Falls Trail Fire, British Columbia, Canada
Jiuzhaigou, China Earthquake
events.description: A 6.5 magnitude earthquake struck China's Jiuzhaigou County located in the southwestern province of Sichuan in China on 08 August. According to the China Earthquake Networks Center, the earthquake hit at a depth of 20km.

events.title: Xhinjiang, China Earthquake
events.description: A magnitude 6.6 earthquake struck the northwestern region of China's Xhinjiang province. Two aftershocks were also reported a few minutes later at 5.2 and 5.3 magnitude.

events.title: Sumatra, Indonesia Earthquake, December 2016
events.description: A 6.4 magnitude earthquake struck off Pidie Jaya District, province of Aceh in Sumatra Island, Indonesia, around 5:00 a.m. local time, on 7 December 2016.

events.title: Central Italy Earthquake
events.description: In the early hours of August 24, 2016, a magnitude 6.2 earthquake occurred in the center of Italy. After the main shock several others occurred in the region producing casualties and widespread damage.

events.title: Myanmar Earthquake
events.description: A magnitude 6.8 earthquake hit Chauk, along the Irrawaddy River in central Myanmar (Burma) on August 24, 2016.

events.title: Tajikistan Earthquake, December 2015
events.description: A 7.2 magnitude earthquake hit Gorno-Badakhshan on December 7 causing extensive damage to residences and infrastructure.

events.title: Aude, France Flooding
events.description: Heavy rainfall is affecting the Herault and Aude Departments, France. This precipitation, equivalent to a number of month's rainfall, has led to flooding over the Aude, Herault and Orb rivers basins.

events.title: Central America Flooding
events.description: Nicaragua, Honduras, Costa Rica and El Salvador have been experiencing heavy rains since the beginning of October 2018.

events.title: Nabeul, Tunisia Flash Floods
events.description: On Saturday 22 September, torrential rain hit north-eastern Tunisia's Cap Bon Peninsula causing water levels to rise 1.7 meters. This was the heaviest rainfall since records were started in 1995.

events.title: Finland Floods
events.description: Extensive spring flooding is expected in the Finnish Lapland due to the snow melt made worse by the warm temperatures and the intermittent rains.

events.title: Freetown, Sierra Leone Landslides and Flooda
Bangladesh Floods and Landslides
events.description: Cyclone Mora struck the eastern coast of Bangladesh on 30 May. The Category 1 hurricane brought powerful winds and torrential rain that have triggered mudslides and flooding.

events.title: Peru, Colombia and Ecuador Flooding
events.description: Several weeks of intense rain have triggered severe floods and mudslides in Peru, Colombia and Ecuador.

events.title: Afghanistan and Pakistan Snowfall, Avalanches and Flooding
events.description: A large number of avalanche, snowfall and rain-related disasters were reported around Afghanistan between 4-7 February, beginning with heavy snowfall on 25 January.

events.title: Russian Federation Floods and Landslides, June 2016
events.description: In the period between 4 and 10 June 2016, heavy rains caused severe disasters in the Republic of Dagestan, the Republic of North Ossetia and the Chechen Republic of the Russian Federation in Northern Caucasus.

events.title: Sri Lanka Floods, May 2016
events.description: Days of heavy rain from Tropical Storm Roanu have caused widespread flooding in Sri Lanka, leaving 37 dead and forcing hundreds of thousands of people to evacuate.

events.title: Bangladesh: Floods and Landslides, Summer 2015
events.description: Since June 24, torrential rains have set off flash floods and landslides in the low-lying areas in the south-eastern districts of Cox Bazar, Bandarban and Chittagong. Tropical Cyclone Komen hit on July 31, affecting more than 1.5 million people across these same coastal districts.

events.title: Tajikistan: Floods and Mudslides
events.description: Prolonged torrential rains caused a number of floods and mudslides between 11 and 13 May 2015 in Khatlon province and Hoit administrative center of the Rasht valley of Tajikistan.

events.title: Rwanda: Floods and Landslides
events.description: On 3 April 2015, heavy rainfall caused flooding and landslides in Nyamasheke and Rubavu districts in Rwanda's Western Province.

events.title: Colombia: Floods and Landslides, Spring 2015
events.description: Flooding, windstorms and landslides affected more than 20,000 people in Colombia in April 2015. The rainy season in the southern and western departments had a particularly strong impact in the Amazonas department near the Peruvian and Brazilian border.

events.title: Central Asia Heatwave
events.description: During the middle of February, temperatures averaged above normal over a wide area of Central Asia, including eastern Kazakhstan, northern Kyrgyzstan, Turkmenistan, and much of Afghanistan.

events.title: Cold Snap in the Northeast U.S.
events.description: As 2017 drew toward a close, Arctic air spilled into the eastern United States and Canada for several days.

events.title: Southwest U.S. Heat Wave
events.description: Extreme heat in the U.S. Southwest is breaking meteorological records, canceling flights, and making life miserable for millions of people.

events.title: Southeast Australia Heatwave
events.description: Extreme heatwave conditions have developed over southwest New South Wales, with severe heatwave conditions continuing through much of the inland parts of South Australia and extend further into southern and western NSW and northern Victoria.

events.title: Morocco and Algeria Cold Wave
events.description: From mid-January, a cold wave has moved across Morocco and Algeria, affecting most cities.

events.title: Mongolia Extreme Cold (Dzud)
events.description: Recent severe winter conditions worsened the situation with average temperature continuously being lower than normal and precipitation forming thicker layer of snow and ice over the grassland.

events.title: India Heatwave, April 2016
events.description: Very high temperatures have been affecting several parts of the country. On April 27, a max. temperature of 45 degrees celsius was observed in Bankura (West Bengal state) and in Wardha (Maharashtra state).

events.title: Morocco Cold Snap, February 2016
events.description: A cold wave has affected Morocco on Saturday 27 February 2016, caused by a polar air mass flow passing from the North Pole to Europe and North Africa, and has generated westerly winds that has brought extreme and exceptionally low temperatures.

events.title: Huaphan Province, Laos Cold Snap
events.description: Low temperatures are currently being experienced throughout northern Laos. The temperature in Xamneua district, Huaphan Province dropped to zero degrees Celsius. Agricultural high altitude areas of Huaphan Province experienced frost therefore crops and vegetation could be potentially damaged.

events.title: Extreme Cold and Snow (Dzud), Mongolia
events.description: Mongolia is experiencing very low temperatures and heavy snowfall since early November 2015, locally named Dzud.

events.title: Alaska Heat Wave, May 2015
events.description: In the third week of May, it was warmer in Fairbanks, Alaska, than in Washington, D.C. The small town of Eagle, Alaska, was hotter on May 23 than it has been on any day in Houston or Dallas this year. In what has become a frequent occurrence in the past few years, temperature profiles in North America appeared to be upside down.
